title.rendered: Jersey vs Canada, World Cup Qualifiers 2023: Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
Jersey vs Canada, World Cup Qualifiers Fantasy Team

We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable Playing XIs for Jersey & Canada

Jersey: Harrison Carylon, Nick Greenwood, Josh Lawrenson, Asa Tribe, Jonty Jenner, Dominic Blampied, Julius Sumerauer, Jake Dunford (wk), Charles Perchard (c), Elliot Miles, Daniel Birrell,

Canada: Aaron Johnson, Pargat Singh, Srimantha Wijeratne (wk), Nicholas Kirton, Ravinderpal Singh, Harsh Thaker, Dillon Heyliger, Saad Bin Zafar (c), Nikhil Dutta, Kaleem Sana, Jeremy Gordon

Also Read:

Afghanistan vs Pakistan, 3rd T20I 2023: Fantasy Tips

Gujarat vs Chennai, Indian T20 League 2023: Fantasy Tips

Pitch Report for United Cricket Club Ground, Windhoek

Venue: United Cricket Club Ground, Windhoek

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 201

2nd innings average score: 261

Wickets per innings: 7

Type: Balanced

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Kaleem Sana has bagged 21 wickets, including two five-fors in his last 10 white-ball games.

Nick Greenwood (326 at 65) and Asa Tribe (321 at 80) seem to be the men in form for Jersey. Collectively, they have slammed two centuries and as many half-centuries in their last five List A games.

Besides taking 16 wickets each in their last 10 white-ball outings, Nikhil Dutta (155 runs at 39) and Saad Bin Zafar (134 at 45) have made valuable contributions with the bat.

Only once in his last 10 white-ball matches has Elliot Miles gone wicketless. In the process, he has taken 16 wickets.

In addition to slamming three fifties in his last five professional List A games, Srimantha Wijeratne has inflicted nine dismissals.

Aside from scoring 234 runs at 47, Harrison Carylon has picked three wickets in his last five List A matches.

Dillon Heyliger has managed only a wicket in his last five limited-overs outings.
